======================
 MailChimp & Mandrill
======================

Note: Updates required to your calling [mailchimp] tags if you used a
      previous version of this tag (API 1.3).

Install these files in the appropriate directories. The 'i' directory
represents the path to your Interchange Server (perhaps /usr/local/interchange).

i/usertag/mailchimp.tag 
	- call this tag from an mv_click for a newsletter signup form, e.g.:
		[set doSubscribe]
			[mailchimp ...]
		[/set]
		<form ...>
		...
		<input type=hidden name=mv_form_profile ...>
		<input type=hidden name=mv_click value=doSubscribe>

i/usertag/mailchimp360.tag
	- IC support for Ecommerce360, allows reporting orders back to MailChimp.
		http://kb.mailchimp.com/article/what-is-ecommerce360-and-how-does-it-work-with-mailchimp

i/usertag/logger.tag
	- logging tag.

other files for queue.

CPAN modules required:
	LWP::UserAgent
	JSON

See POD in mailchimp.tag and mandrill.tag for documentation (`perldoc i/usertag/mailchimp.tag`).
